INSERT INTO `Directions` (RecipeID, SortOrder, Direction) VALUES ('20533', '5', 'Add the chili flakes, red wine and 1 teaspoon of salt. Stir, cover, reduce heat to low and cook until they are fully tender. Taste and adjust salt and chili flakes.Grease a 13" x 18" half-sheet pan (aka jelly roll pan).'),
('20533', '6', 'Pour in half of the polenta and spread it into an even layer. Top with the sauteed greens (leaving behind any excess liquid) and the Caciocavallo cheese, distributing them as evenly as possible. Cover with the remaining polenta and use a spatula to form an even layer.Cover with plastic wrap and allow to chill until the polenta has set up firm, at least a couple of hours.'),
('20533', '7', 'Bake at 375 until heated through, then broil until the top layer of cheese is browned, then cut into triangles and serve.'),
('20545', '1', 'In a small saucepan, cover the lentils with 2 1/2 cups of water and bring to a boil. Cover and cook over low heat until the lentils are tender, about 30 minutes.'),
('20545', '2', 'Meanwhile, in a medium saucepan, heat 2 tablespoons of the olive oil.'),
('20545', '3', 'Add the shiitake and season with salt. Cover and cook over moderate heat, stirring, until the mushrooms are tender and starting to brown, 5 minutes.'),
('20545', '4', 'Add the remaining 1 tablespoon of olive oil along with the garlic, cumin, coriander, pepper and turmeric and cook, stirring, until fragrant, 1 minute.'),
('20545', '5', 'Add the greens and cook, stirring, until wilted, 2 minutes.'),
('20545', '6', 'Add the lentils and their cooking liquid to the mushrooms and simmer for 3 minutes.'),
('20545', '7', 'Add up to 1/4 cup of water if the lentils are too dry. Season with salt. Ladle the lentils into bowls, garnish with the parsley and serve.'),
('20547', '1', 'Light a grill or preheat a grill pan.'),
('20547', '2', 'Brush the chicken breasts with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Lightly brush the grate or grill pan with vegetable oil and cook the chicken over a hot fire until browned and just cooked through, about 3 minutes per side.'),
('20547', '3', 'Transfer to a plate and let cool to room temperature.'),
('20547', '4', 'In a medium saucepan of boiling water, blanch the chard leaves for 1 1/2 minutes; blanch the spinach for 30 seconds.'),
('20547', '5', 'Drain well.'),
('20547', '6', 'Let cool slightly, then squeeze dry and coarsely chop. In a large bowl, mix the chard with the 2 tablespoons of olive oil and season with salt. Stir in the drained yogurt and the garlic and season with salt and pepper.'),
('20547', '7', 'For each wrap, arrange 2 sheets of lavash on a work surface, overlapping the short sides by 5 inches. Tuck half of the cheese slices under the overlapping flap to within 1/2 inch of the edge.'),
('20547', '8', 'Spread half of the avocado slices on top of the overlapping flap and sprinkle with half of the lemon juice; season generously with salt, pepper and hot sauce. Top with half of the tomato slices and season with salt and pepper. For each wrap, fold 1 of the flaps of lavash over the tomatoes and spread half of the chard on the lavash. Top with a chicken breast, trimming it to fit. Fold the second lavash flap over the chicken. Repeat to assemble the second sandwich. Tightly wrap the sandwiches in foil and refrigerate until firm or for up to 4 hours.'),
('20547', '9', 'Light a grill. Unwrap the sandwiches and brush both sides with olive oil. Lightly brush the grate with vegetable oil. Grill the sandwiches over a low fire, cheese side down, for about 4 minutes, or until the cheese melts and the lavash is crisp. Using 2 large spatulas, carefully flip the sandwiches and grill for 5 minutes longer, or until they are heated through and very crisp.'),
('20547', '10', 'Transfer to a cutting board. Using a serrated knife, cut each sandwich crosswise into thirds and serve.'),
('20548', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 37'),
('20548', '2', 'Cut the feta into large triangles and arrange them in a single layer in a baking dish. In a small bowl, combine 2 tablespoons of the olive oil with the oregano, crushed red pepper, lemon zest and half of the garlic slices.'),
('20548', '3', 'Spread the marinade all over the feta cheese and let stand for at least 5 minutes or up to an hour.'),
('20548', '4', 'In a large, deep skillet, heat the remaining 2 tablespoons of olive oil until shimmering.'),
('20548', '5', 'Add the remaining garlic and cook over moderate heat, stirring, until pale golden, 1 to 2 minutes.'),
('20548', '6', 'Add the greens, a handful at a time, and cook, stirring, until tender, about 4 minutes.'),
('20548', '7', 'Pour off any liquid, season with salt and pepper and keep warm.'),
('20548', '8', 'Bake the feta for about 5 minutes, or until heated through. Spoon the greens onto 4 plates and add the feta, olives and bread.'),
('20548', '9', 'Drizzle any feta juices over the bread and serve immediately.'),
('20549', '1', 'Save Recipe'),
('20549', '2', 'Print Recipe'),
('20549', '3', 'Tortino d''Azzima (Matzo Pie)'),
('20549', '4', 'Matzo Pie Ingredients'),
('20549', '5', 'Extra virgin olive oil (to taste)2 boxes (about 10 oz. each) matzo (more or less)2 lbs. cleaned Swiss chard or baby spinach2 lbs. artichoke hearts (frozen is ok)2 lbs. asparagus or mushroom, cleaned and sliced1 cup dry white wine6 garlic cloves2 quarts cold chicken broth (for soaking the matzo- sub vegetable broth for vegan mod.)3 eggs (optional)Salt and pepper to taste'),
('20549', '6', 'Sugo d''Arrosto (Roast Juice) Ingredients'),
('20549', '7', 'Extra virgin olive oil'),
('20549', '8', 'Garlic Cloves'),
('20549', '9', 'Rosemary4 oz. ground meat (optional)1 piece marrow bone (optional)Salt and pepper to taste'),
('20549', '10', 'You will also need'),
('20549', '11', 'Three large skillets with lids, 10"x12" baking pan (or similar size)'),
('20549', '12', 'Servings: 8'),
('20549', '13', 'Kosher Key: Meat (Pareve/Vegan with modification)'),
('20552', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('20552', '2', 'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.'),
('20552', '3', 'Heat oil in a large saute pan over medium-low heat.'),
('20552', '4', 'Add garlic and cook until soft and golden, about 1 minute.'),
('20552', '5', 'Add diced tomatoes with juice, tomato sauce, red peppers, chili peppers, cumin, coriander and 1/4 teaspoon each salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium-low and simmer for 10 minutes until sauce thickens slightly.'),
('20552', '6', 'Remove from heat, and remove chile peppers.'),
('20552', '7', 'Place Swiss chard on the bottom of a 9 by 13-inch glass baking dish. Season fish fillets with remaining salt and pepper and place in on top of chard. Cover with sauce and bake, covered, until fish is just cooked and chard is wilted, about 15 minutes.'),
('20552', '8', 'Remove cover and bake an additional 5 minutes. Sprinkle with cilantro and serve.'),
('20553', '1', 'Cut 4 slices of bacon into pieces and cook on medium heat in your soup pan.  I usually use a cast iron dutch oven to cook my soups.'),
('20553', '2', 'Once the bacon has slightly browned, about 4 minutes, add 3/4 of a small to medium sized sweet onion, half of a bulb of fennel, 1 leek, 3 carrots peeled, and 3 celery stalks all coarsely chopped.'),
('20553', '3', 'Add 3 tablespoons of olive oil, cover pan and let cook over medium heat stirring occasionally.  This process will release the essence of the vegetables and also infuse the flavor of bacon into the pan.'),
('20553', '4', 'Let cook for about 25 minutes.'),
('20553', '5', 'Pour in 8 cups of broth to the pot.'),
('20553', '6', 'Add the rind from the Parmesan.'),
('20553', '7', 'Remove the lid and turn the heat up to medium-high.  Stir occasionally and allow to cook for 20-25 minutes.'),
('20553', '8', 'While the broth is cooking.  Prepare your soup ingredients.  Chop 1 leek, 1/2 of a small to medium sweet onion, the rest of the fennel bulb, 3 carrots, the zucchini, and around 4 large green Swiss Chard leaves, stems removed.  Break the softer ends of the asparagus up into bite size pieces.  This part of the process is best done with your hands as you can feel when the asparagus begins to get tougher, at which point you do not want to use it in the soup.'),
('20553', '9', 'Boil a pot of salted water to blanch the vegetables and prepare an ice bath to put them in after they have blanched.  Once the water is boiling blanch the carrots for 4 minutes, then the zucchini for 3-4 minutes, the chard for 3- 4 minutes, and the asparagus for 2 minutes.  Set aside until ready.  If you are using fresh peas you would also blanch them at this point for 3 minutes.  I used frozen because the ones at the market today didn''t look so fresh.'),
('20553', '10', 'Drain the broth into a large bowl.  Make sure to really press down on the vegetable/bacon mixture to release all the broth being held in.  Set aside broth.  Discard the cooked vegetable and bacon mixture.'),
('20553', '11', 'Saute the chopped leeks, onion, and fennel in 2 tablespoons olive oil.  Once they have softened and slightly browned add 3 finely chopped cloves of garlic and cook for 1 minute.  Return the broth to the pot and cook for around 4 minutes.'),
('20553', '12', 'Add in the cooked cannellini beans and cook on medium-high for 10 minutes.  Season with approx. 2 teaspoons salt and about 40 clicks of fresh ground black pepper.  Remember the pistou and Parmesan will add saltiness to the soup so don''t go overboard.'),
('20553', '13', 'Put 1 cup frozen peas into the broth and cook for 1 minute.'),
('20553', '14', 'Add the blanched vegetables to the broth and turn off heat.'),
('20553', '15', 'Serve with a spoonful of basil and mint pistou, a sprinkling of fresh Parmesan, and some crusty bread.  A good and inexpensive bottle of Provencal white wine also goes nicely while cooking and eating this soup!'),
('20553', '16', 'Place all ingredients in a food processor or mini-chopper.  You may have to add in the herb leaves in batches.'),
('20553', '17', 'Mix until fairly well chopped and properly combined.'),
('20553', '18', 'Serve over soup.'),
('20555', '1', 'Combine 10 cups water, onion, and the next 4 ingredients (10 cups water through bay leaf) in a large Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 30 minutes.'),
('20555', '2', 'Remove 2 cups cooking liquid; set aside.'),
('20555', '3', 'Add squash and next 6 ingredients (squash through chickpeas) to onion mixture. Simmer 25 minutes or until squash is tender. Stir in chard, cilantro, 2 teaspoons salt, and black pepper; cook 5 minutes or until chard wilts. Stir in juice. Discard bay leaf.'),
('20555', '4', 'Place couscous in a large bowl.'),
('20555', '5', 'Combine reserved cooking liquid and remaining 1 1/2 cups water in a small saucepan; bring to a boil. Stir in remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt and oil.'),
('20555', '6', 'Pour water mixture over couscous; stir well to combine. Cover and let stand 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed. Fluff with a fork.'),
('20555', '7', 'Serve vegetable mixture over couscous. Top with crumbled cheese.'),
('20558', '1', 'Heat a nonstick skillet over high heat; add 1 tablespoon olive oil to pan.'),
('20558', '2', 'Add onions to pan; saut until soft, about 8 minutes. Reduce heat to medium; add garlic. Cook until onions are caramelized, about 20 minutes.'),
('20558', '3', 'Add Swiss chard leaves; cook until wilted and tender, about 5 minutes.'),
('20558', '4', 'Place 6 cups water in a pan; bring to a boil.'),
('20558', '5', 'Add lentils to pan. Reduce heat, and simmer; cook until tender, about 15 minutes.'),
('20558', '6', 'Add 2 teaspoons salt; let sit 5 minutes to absorb.'),
('20558', '7', 'Drain lentils; cool on a baking sheet.'),
('20558', '8', 'Combine chickpeas, lentils, chard-and-onion mixture, pomegranate molasses, lemon juice, 2 tablespoons olive oil, and 1/8 teaspoon each of salt and pepper.'),
('20561', '1', 'Soak berries in red wine.'),
('20561', '2', 'Heat the extra-virgin olive oil in a large deep skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('20561', '3', 'Add bacon and crisp 3 to 4 minutes.'),
('20561', '4', 'Add onion, garlic and cook 3 to 4 minutes to soften.'),
('20561', '5', 'Add red chard and wilt, 2 to 3 minutes. Season greens with salt, pepper and nutmeg. Stir in cranberries and wine. Cook for 1 minute then add in stock and simmer a few minutes to combine flavors.'),
('20562', '1', 'In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook the orecchiette until al dente.'),
('20562', '2', 'Drain, reserving 1/4 cup of the cooking water.'),
('20562', '3', 'Meanwhile, in a medium saucepan, melt the butter.'),
('20562', '4', 'Add the sliced scallions and garlic and cook over low heat until softened, about 5 minutes.'),
('20562', '5', 'Add the white wine and cook over moderate heat until reduced by half, about 5 minutes.'),
('20562', '6', 'Add 1/2 cup of water and puree the mixture in a blender until smooth. Season the scallion sauce with salt and pepper.'),
('20562', '7', 'Wipe out the pasta pot and heat the olive oil in it.'),
('20562', '8', 'Add the arugula and Swiss chard; cook over high heat until wilted, 5 minutes.'),
('20562', '9', 'Add the pasta, scallion sauce and the reserved pasta cooking water and simmer, tossing and stirring, until the sauce is thick, about 3 minutes. Stir in the mascarpone, season the pasta with salt and pepper and serve.'),
('20568', '1', 'In a salad bowl, whisk the mustard and vinegar. Gradually whisk in the olive oil, followed by the walnut and hazelnut oils. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('20568', '2', 'Add the greens and flowers, toss gently and serve'),
('20570', '1', 'Whisk together miso, mustard, Sriracha, sake, and 1/2 cup plus 1 tbsp. mirin in a small saucepan.'),
('20570', '2', 'Add ginger. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer 6 to 8 minutes, or until sauce is just thick enough to coat a spoon. Strain through a fine-mesh strainer, pushing against solids.'),
('20570', '3', 'Let glaze cool to room temperature.'),
('20570', '4', 'Bring remaining 1 1/2 tbsp. mirin and the vinegar to a boil in a very small saucepan.'),
('20570', '5', 'Add goji berries. Return to a boil and remove from heat.'),
('20570', '6', 'Let cool, uncovered.'),
('20570', '7', 'Put rack in middle of oven, then preheat oven to 40'),
('20570', '8', 'Line a rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper.'),
('20570', '9', 'Cut 1 parsnip lengthwise into 8 spears.'),
('20570', '10', 'Cut remaining parsnips into 3/4-in. chunks.'),
('20570', '11', 'Transfer spears and chunks to baking sheet, season with salt and white pepper, and toss with sesame oil.'),
('20570', '12', 'Spread in a single layer, with spears cut side down.'),
('20570', '13', 'Bake parsnips 20 minutes, turning 2 or 3 times.'),
('20570', '14', 'Meanwhile, bring a medium saucepan of water to a boil.'),
('20570', '15', 'Cut tofu into 4 rectangular slabs, each about the size of a deck of cards, and put in a large, shallow bowl.'),
('20570', '16', 'Pour hot water over tofu and let soak 15 minutes.'),
('20570', '17', 'Drain on a clean dish towel or a double layer of paper towels set on a plate.'),
('20570', '18', 'Remove parsnip spears from oven when tips begin to brown; remove chunks when just fork-tender.'),
('20570', '19', 'Let chunks cool 5 minutes, then pure in a food processor with 2 tbsp. miso-mustard glaze and 1 cup hot water until smooth but able to hold a peak when spooned onto a plate (add up to 1/2 cup hot water if needed). Keep warm, covered.'),
('20570', '20', 'Put tatsoi in a large saucepan with 1/4 cup hot water and cook over low heat, covered, stirring occasionally, until wilted, 5 minutes; drain and return to pan. Stir in goji berries and some of their pickling liquid.'),
('20570', '21', 'Pour remaining miso-mustard glaze into a medium frying pan. Blot moisture from tofu with paper towels and add tofu to glaze. Bring to a simmer over medium heat and cook, spooning glaze over tofu, until glaze sticks to top of tofu and has reduced by one-half to two-thirds.'),
('20570', '22', 'Spoon parsnip pure onto plates. With a spatula, set tofu on parsnip pure.'),
('20570', '23', 'Drizzle glaze over tofu and top with tatsoi and goji berries, then add parsnip spears.'),
('20570', '24', '*Find at Whole Foods Market, health food stores, and Asian markets.'),
('20573', '1', 'Cut shallots into 1/8-inch-thick slices. In a heavy 10-inch skillet cook shallots in oil over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until golden, 15 to 20 minutes. With a slotted spoon transfer shallots to paper towels to drain and season with salt. Reserve 3 tablespoons oil for dressing salad and cool shallots to room temperature. Shallots may be fried 2 days ahead and kept in an airtight container at room temperature.'),
('20573', '2', 'Just before serving, in a large bowl toss together greens, sprouts, reserved oil, vinegar, and sea salt. Sprinkle shallots over salad.'),
('20583', '1', 'Peel turnips, and cut in half.'),
('20583', '2', 'Place turnips in a single layer in a 12-inch heavy skillet; add water to reach halfway up turnips (about 1 1/2 cups).'),
('20583', '3', 'Add butter and next 3 ingredients. Cover and bring to a boil over high heat; reduce heat to medium-high, and cook, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes. Uncover and cook, stirring often, 8 minutes or until turnips are tender and water has evaporated. Cook, stirring often, 5 more minutes or until turnips are golden. Stir in sorghum and 3 Tbsp. water; toss turnips to coat.'),
('20583', '4', 'Serve immediately.'),
('20583', '5', 'Garnish, if desired.'),
('20584', '1', 'Wrap 1 pancetta slice around 1 turnip wedge, covering most of turnip. Repeat with remaining pancetta slices and turnip wedges.'),
('20584', '2', 'Line rimmed baking sheet with waxed paper.'),
('20584', '3', 'Whisk egg in medium bowl to blend and place sesame seeds in another medium bowl. Dip each pancetta-wrapped turnip wedge into beaten egg to coat, then dip into sesame seeds, turning to coat generously on all sides.'),
('20584', '4', 'Place on prepared baking sheet. DO AHEAD: Turnips can be prepared 2 hours ahead. Cover and keep chilled.'),
('20584', '5', 'Preheat oven to 350°F.'),
('20584', '6', 'Pour enough vegetable oil into heavy medium saucepan to reach depth of 2 inches. Attach deep-fry thermometer to side of pan and heat oil to 350°F. Working in batches, add sesame-coated turnip wedges to oil, and deep-fry until sesame seeds are golden, about 1 minute (turnips will be very crunchy).'),
('20584', '7', 'Transfer turnips to paper towels to drain. Arrange turnips on rimmed baking sheet and bake just until turnips are beginning to soften, about 7 minutes. Sprinkle generously with salt and pepper.'),
('20586', '1', 'Combine rutabagas, 1 tsp. salt, and 6 cups water in a large Dutch oven; bring to a boil, and cook 25 minutes.'),
('20586', '2', 'Add turnips, and cook 20 more minutes or until vegetables are tender; drain.'),
('20586', '3', 'Combine vegetables, cheese, and next 4 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; mash with a potato masher (or beat at medium speed with an electric mixer) to desired consistency. Stir in bourbon, if desired.'),
('20588', '1', 'Place first 3 ingredients in a Dutch oven; cover with water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer 15 minutes or until tender.'),
('20588', '2', 'Drain.'),
('20588', '3', 'Stir in butter and remaining ingredients; mash mixture with a potato masher to desired consistency.'),
('20591', '1', 'Stir together miso and 2 tablespoon butter.'),
('20591', '2', 'Discard turnip stems and coarsely chop leaves. Halve turnips (leave whole if tiny) and put in a 12-inch heavy skillet along with water, mirin, remaining tablespoon butter, and 1/8 teaspoon salt. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, then boil, covered, 10 minutes.'),
('20591', '3', 'Add greens by handfuls, turning and stirring with tongs and adding more as volume in skillet reduces. Cover and cook 1 minute. Uncover and continue boiling, stirring occasionally, until turnips are tender and liquid is reduced to a glaze, about 5 minutes. Stir in miso butter and cook 1 minute.'),
('20592', '1', 'Peel the potatoes and turnips and cut into -inch dice.'),
('20592', '2', 'Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Using kitchen scissors, snip off -inch pieces of bacon into the skillet. Cook until nearly crisp, about 5 minutes.'),
('20592', '3', 'Drain off the fat.'),
('20592', '4', 'Add the potatoes and turnips to the bacon and saut for about 3 minutes.'),
('20592', '5', 'Add the chicken broth, bring to a boil, cover and cook for 10 minutes until vegetables are almost tender.'),
('20592', '6', 'Remove the lid.'),
('20592', '7', 'Add the cream and cook over high heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally until the liquid is almost evaporated.'),
('20592', '8', 'Season to taste with salt and pepper.'),
('20592', '9', 'var article'),
('20592', '10', 'Type_27_data = {};'),
('20592', '11', 'article'),
('20592', '12', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0;'),
('20598', '1', 'Melt butter in a 12-inch heavy skillet over medium heat, then add turnips, water, lemon juice, and 1/2 teaspoon salt and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, 30 minutes. Increase heat to medium and stir turnips, then briskly simmer, uncovered, until all of liquid has evaporated and turnips are glazed and just tender, 20 to 35 minutes (they should be cooked through but still retain their shape).'),
('20601', '1', 'In a large saute pan, heat pan on medium and add the mustard seeds. Toast seeds until fragrant, about 1 minute.'),
('20601', '2', 'Add butter and oil. When butter is melted, add the turnips and cabbage and saute until cabbage begins to wilt, about 5 minutes.'),
('20601', '3', 'Mix in vinegar and stock. Bring mixture to a simmer, cover and braise until a knife inserted in a turnip comes out easily and cabbage is wilted and tender, about 25 minutes. Season, to taste, with salt.'),
('20602', '1', 'Preheat oven to 350°F.'),
('20602', '2', 'Combine honey, lemon juice, and melted butter in large bowl.'),
('20602', '3', 'Add pears; toss to coat. Arrange pears in single layer on large rimmed baking sheet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Roast pears 30 minutes. Turn pears to coat with juices and roast until very tender, about 35 minutes longer.'),
('20602', '4', 'Transfer pears and caramelized liquids to food processor; blend until smooth. (Pear puree can be made 2 days ahead. Cover and refrigerate.)'),
('20602', '5', 'Cook potatoes and turnips in separate large pots of generously salted water until tender, about 25 minutes.'),
('20602', '6', 'Drain well.'),
('20602', '7', 'Transfer turnips to processor; puree until smooth. Mash potatoes with room-temperature butter in large bowl until smooth. Stir in pureed turnips. Season to taste with salt and pepper. (Can be prepared 6 hours ahead. Cover and refrigerate. Rewarm in microwave before continuing.)'),
('20602', '8', 'Rewarm pear puree.'),
('20602', '9', 'Place potato-turnip mixture in large serving bowl. Swirl in pear puree and serve.'),
('20603', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 37'),
('20603', '2', 'In a saucepan, combine the stock, wine, garlic, orange zest and bay leaves and bring to a boil. Reduce to 2 cups over high heat, 30 minutes.'),
('20603', '3', 'Add the reduction to a large roasting pan. Arrange the duck in the pan skin side up. Cover and braise until hot, 30 minutes.'),
('20603', '4', 'Preheat the broiler.'),
('20603', '5', 'Transfer the duck to a large rimmed baking sheet. Strain the braising liquid into a saucepan, pressing on the garlic to mash it into the sauce.  Bring the sauce to a simmer. In a bowl, blend the butter with the flour; whisk the paste  into the sauce. Simmer, whisking, until thickened, 3 minutes. Season with salt and pepper and keep warm, whisking occasionally.'),
('20603', '6', 'Broil the duck, rotating the pan, until the skin is crisp, 4 minutes.'),
('20603', '7', 'Transfer to plates, top with the sauce and serve with turnips.'),
('20606', '1', 'Preheat oven to 375  degrees F (190 degrees C).'),
('20606', '2', 'Place turnip and potatoes in a large pot with enough water to cover, and bring to a boil. Cook 25 to 30 minutes, until tender.'),
('20606', '3', 'Remove from heat, and drain.'),
('20606', '4', 'Mix milk, 2 tablespoons butter, and sugar with the turnip and potatoes. Season with salt and pepper. Mash until slightly lumpy.'),
('20606', '5', 'Transfer turnip mixture to a small baking dish. Dot with remaining butter. Cover loosely, and bake 15 minutes in the preheated oven.'),
('20606', '6', 'Remove cover, and continue baking about 8 minutes, until lightly browned.'),
('20609', '1', 'Sauté the onions in butter: In a large, heavy, thick-bottomed pot, melt the butter on medium heat until it foams. When the butter foam subsides, add the onions and cook until translucent but not browned, about 5 minutes.'),
('20612', '1', 'Melt butter in a wide 5-quart heavy pot over moderate heat, then add turnips, stirring until well coated.'),
('20612', '2', 'Add broth, sugar, and salt and bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer, covered, until turnips are just tender, 25 to 30 minutes.'),
('20612', '3', 'Continue to boil turnips, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until liquid is reduced enough to just glaze turnips, about 15 minutes. Sprinkle with scallions and parsley.'),
('20618', '1', 'Heat the olive oil in a large saucepan until shimmering.'),
('20618', '2', 'Add the onion and garlic and cook over moderately high heat, stirring occasionally, until softened, about 6 minutes.'),
('20618', '3', 'Add the turnips and cook, stirring frequently, until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.'),
('20618', '4', 'Add the wine and cook until almost evaporated, about 5 minutes.'),
('20618', '5', 'Add the 4 cups of chicken stock and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to moderately low and simmer until the turnips are tender, about 25 minutes.'),
('20618', '6', 'Working in batches, puree the soup in a blender or food processor, then strain it through a fine sieve. Return the soup to a clean saucepan, stir in the scallions and cook over moderate heat for 5 minutes.'),
('20618', '7', 'Whisk in the crme frache until fully incorporated; thin the soup with stock if necessary. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('20618', '8', 'Ladle the soup into shallow bowls and serve with the Cheese Crisps.'),
('20621', '1', 'Place the turnips in a 2-gallon ceramic jar. In a mixing bowl, stir together the water, vinegar, sugar, salt and crushed grapes and pour over turnips. Cover and refrigerate for 48 hours.'),
('20621', '2', 'Two days later: In a 12 to 14-inch saute pan, heat the olive oil until smoking over medium heat.'),
('20621', '3', 'Add onions and garlic and cook until softened, about 8 minutes.'),
('20621', '4', 'Add flour and caraway and stir through.'),
('20621', '5', 'Drain turnips and add to pan. Cook until very soft, careful not to break the turnips, about 1 hour.'),
('20621', '6', 'Serve with grilled sausages or pork shank (stinco).'),
('20622', '1', 'Add the turnips and potatoes to a large pot of cold salted water. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer and cook until soft and tender, about 20 minutes.'),
('20622', '2', 'In a small saucepan, add the butter over medium-high heat. Once melted and foamy, add the shallots and sage and saute until the shallot is tender, the sage is fragrant and the butter begins to brown. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('20622', '3', 'Add the milk and bring to a simmer. (This will infuse the milk with the sage flavor.)'),
('20622', '4', 'Drain the turnips and potatoes in a colander in the sink.'),
('20622', '5', 'Add the turnips and potatoes back to the pot they were cooked in.'),
('20622', '6', 'Add the hot milk and roughly mash the vegetables. If you prefer a smoother texture, use an immersion blender and puree until smooth and silky. Taste for seasoning, add salt and pepper.'),
('20628', '1', 'In a large heavy stockpot or casserole, melt the butter until it foams. When the foam subsides, add the onions and cook over moderate heat until softened but not browned, about 5 minutes.'),
('20628', '2', 'Add the turnips and potatoes and stir to coat with the butter.'),
('20628', '3', 'Add 2 teaspoons of salt, cover and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until tender, about 20 minutes.'),
('20628', '4', 'Stir in the chicken stock and bring to a simmer. Cover partially and cook over moderate heat until the vegetables are very tender, about 10 minutes.'),
('20628', '5', 'Working in batches, puree the soup in a blender until perfectly smooth. Return the soup to the pot and season with salt and the nutmeg. Ladle the soup into shallow bowls and garnish with the basil before serving.'),
('20630', '1', 'Peel and cube the turnip. Cook in a saucepan in salted water until very tender.'),
('20630', '2', 'Drain then mash with the butter or margarine, salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste. Set aside.'),
('20630', '3', 'In a skillet fry the bacon until nice and crispy.'),
('20630', '4', 'Remove from the skillet and crumble.  Reserve 2 tablespoons of the bacon grease.'),
('20630', '5', 'To the skillet with the 2 tablespoons of bacon grease add the mashed turnip and crumpled bacon. Stir and heat to the desired temperature before serving.'),
('20632', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('20632', '2', 'Heat the oil and unsalted butter in a saucepan over medium-low heat until it reaches 220 degrees F. Reduce the heat to low, add the shallots, and cook until they are a rich golden brown, 30 to 40 minutes. The temperature should stay below 260 degrees F. Stir the shallots occasionally to make sure they brown evenly.'),
('20632', '3', 'Remove them from the oil with a slotted spoon, drain well, and spread out to cool on paper towels. Once they have dried and crisped, they can be stored at room temperature, covered, for several days.'),
('20632', '4', 'Peel the turnips to remove the waxy skins and cut them into generous 1-inch chunks.'),
('20632', '5', 'Place them in a saucepan with water to cover and 1 teaspoon of salt. Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, until easily pierced by a paring knife, about 35 minutes.'),
('20632', '6', 'Drain.'),
('20632', '7', 'In a separate saucepan, heat the milk and salted butter over low heat until the butter has melted and the milk just begins to simmer.'),
('20632', '8', 'Puree the turnips in several batches in a food processor fitted with the steel blade. With the motor running, add the melted butter and milk in a steady stream. The turnips should be smooth.'),
('20632', '9', 'Return the puree to the saucepan, season with 1 teaspoon salt and the pepper, and reheat, stirring, over medium heat.'),
('20632', '10', 'Serve piping hot, sprinkled generously with crispy shallots.'),
('20634', '1', 'Trim the turnips, leaving about 1/2 inch of the stems. Halve the turnips lengthwise and transfer them to a 2-quart glass jar. Dissolve 2 tablespoons plus 1 teaspoon of the salt in 1 quart of the water and pour the brine over the turnips. Cover tightly and let stand at room temperature for 24 hours.'),
('20634', '2', 'Drain and rinse the turnips. Wash out the jar. Return the turnips to the jar. Dissolve the remaining 2 tablespoons plus 1 teaspoon of salt in the remaining 1 quart of water.'),
('20634', '3', 'Add the garlic, scallions, ginger and chile to the turnips.'),
('20634', '4', 'Pour enough of the brine into the jar to cover the turnips. Cover tightly and let stand at room temperature for 24 hours, then refrigerate for up to 5 days.'),
('20636', '1', 'Melt margarine in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.'),
('20636', '2', 'Add leek and shallots; saut 4 minutes.'),
('20636', '3', 'Add turnips; saut 2 minutes. Stir in water and broth; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer 30 minutes or until turnips are tender.'),
('20636', '4', 'Place one-third of turnip mixture in a blender; process until smooth.'),
('20636', '5', 'Pour pured mixture into a large bowl; repeat procedure with remaining turnip mixture. Return turnip pure to pan; stir in milk and pepper. Cook until thoroughly heated. Ladle into soup bowls; garnish with fresh chives, if desired.'),
('20638', '1', 'In a small bowl, mix together 6 tablespoons of the butter and 3 tablespoons of the dill to blend. Season to taste with salt and pepper. (The dill butter may be made 2 days ahead if covered and refrigerated.)'),
('20638', '2', 'In a skillet, saut the bacon, if using, over medium heat until brown and crisp. Using a slotted spoon, transfer to paper towels to drain.'),
('20638', '3', 'Let the bacon cool to room temperature.'),
('20638', '4', 'In a large nonstick skillet, melt the remaining 2 tablespoons of butter over medium-high heat.'),
('20638', '5', 'Add the turnips and saut for about 9 minutes, or until tender and golden. If you find the turnips taste sharp, add a little sugar.'),
('20638', '6', 'Add the peas and dill butter and cook, stirring, for about 3 minutes, or until the peas are heated through and the butter melts.'),
('20638', '7', 'Stir in the bacon, if using. Season to taste with salt and pepper.'),
('20638', '8', 'Transfer to a bowl, garnish with the remaining tablespoon of dill, and serve.'),
('20638', '9', 'var article'),
('20638', '10', 'Type_27_data = {};'),
('20638', '11', 'article'),
('20638', '12', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0;'),
('20639', '1', 'Place quartered turnips and radishes in a bowl and sprinkle with salt. (If using jicama or kholrabi, peel first and cut into 1 X 1/4 inch pieces. If using carrots, cut into 1 X 1/4 inch and blanch for two minutes before salting).'),
('20639', '2', 'Let sit for one hour.'),
('20639', '3', 'Drain and place in jar.'),
('20639', '4', 'Add all other ingredients to a small saucepan and bring to the boil.'),
('20639', '5', 'Pour directly into Mason jar. Cap jar and let stand at room temperature until cool. Refrigerate. They will be ready to eat in three days.'),
('20641', '1', 'Place the turnips in a pot and cover with water; bring to a boil over high heat and cook until turnips turn yellowish orange and are soft, 10 to 12 minutes.'),
('20641', '2', 'Drain water, leaving turnips in the pot.'),
('20641', '3', 'Stir the butter and caraway seeds into the turnips. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Use a potato masher to mash turnips to desired consistency. Stir in the cream and mash again, blending well.'),
('20643', '1', 'Place turnips, potatoes, and garlic in a 5-quart pot. Cover with cold water to 2 inches above the vegetables; bring to a boil.'),
('20643', '2', 'Add salt; simmer, uncovered, until tender (about 15 minutes).'),
('20643', '3', 'Drain the vegetables in a colander; return to pot. Cook over medium heat to remove excess water, stirring well (about 5 minutes). Stir in the remaining ingredients; mash with a potato masher until smooth.'),
('20643', '4', 'Transfer mixture to a serving dish.'),
('20654', '1', 'Place the turnips in a large pot of cold water and bring to a boil. Cook until they are forktender, about 15 minutes.'),
('20654', '2', 'Drain.'),
('20654', '3', 'Put the turnips through a ricer or pure in a food processor; set aside.'),
('20654', '4', 'Meanwhile, in a deep saucepan over medium heat, saut the shallots in the butter until they turn golden brown, about 15 minutes. With a slotted spoon, remove the shallots and drain on paper towels.'),
('20654', '5', 'Set a heavy saucepan over medium heat.'),
('20654', '6', 'Add the cream and 1 tablespoon butter and bring to a simmer.'),
('20654', '7', 'Add the turnips, stir briskly, and season with the salt, pepper, and nutmeg.'),
('20654', '8', 'Spoon the pure onto serving plates and garnish liberally with the shallots and lightly with the parsley.'),
('20654', '9', 'Serve immediately.'),
('20654', '10', 'var article'),
('20654', '11', 'Type_27_data = {};'),
('20654', '12', 'article'),
('20654', '13', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0;'),
('20656', '1', 'Warm the chicken stock in a sauce pan over medium-low heat.'),
('20656', '2', 'Pour the olive oil into a large skillet and turn the heat to medium.  Toss in the onion and cook until softened, about 10 minutes.'),
('20656', '3', 'Add the turnips and cook for 2 minutes.  Ladle in some of the hot chicken stock and cook until absorbed.  Continue until all of the stock has been added, about 10 minutes.'),
('20656', '4', 'Season with salt and pepper.'),
('20656', '5', 'Add the butter and grated cheese stir occasionally for a minute.'),
('20656', '6', 'Remove from the heat, garnish with parsley, and serve.'),
('20663', '1', 'Bring greens, ham hock, water, and 1/4 teaspoon salt to a boil in a large heavy pot. Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, until greens are almost tender, about 20 minutes.'),
('20663', '2', 'Meanwhile, peel apples and cut into 1/2-inch pieces.'),
('20663', '3', 'Add turnips and apples to greens with vinegar, sugar, and 1/2 teaspoon each of salt and pepper and cook at a bare simmer, covered, stirring and turning ham hock occasionally, until turnips and apples are tender but not falling apart, about 20 minutes more.'),
('20663', '4', 'Remove from heat and stir in butter and salt to taste.'),
('20663', '5', 'Remove ham hock and finely chop any tender meat, discarding skin, bone, and tough meat.'),
('20663', '6', 'Add chopped meat to pot.'),
('20666', '1', 'Heat oil over medium-high heat in a large, deep saute pan until shimmering.'),
('20666', '2', 'Add turnips, then onion; saute, stirring very little at first, then more frequently, until vegetables start to turn golden brown, 7 to 8 minutes.'),
('20666', '3', 'Reduce heat to low and add butter, sugar and garlic; continue cooking until all vegetables are a rich spotty caramel color, about 10 minutes longer.'),
('20666', '4', 'Add paprika, thyme and cayenne pepper; continue to saute until fragrant, 30 seconds to 1 minute longer.'),
('20666', '5', 'Add broth; bring to a simmer over medium-high heat. Reduce heat to low and simmer, partially covered, until turnips are tender, about 10 minutes.'),
('20666', '6', 'Using an immersion blender or traditional blender, puree until very smooth, 30 seconds to 1 minute. (If using a traditional blender, vent it either by removing the lid''s pop-out center or by lifting one edge of the lid. Drape the blender canister with a kitchen towel. To ''clean'' the canister, pour in a little half-and-half, blend briefly, then add to the soup.)'),
('20666', '7', 'Return to pan (or a soup pot); add enough half-and-half so the mixture is souplike, yet thick enough to float garnish. Taste, and add salt and pepper if needed.'),
('20666', '8', 'Heat through, ladle into bowls, garnish and serve.'),
('20670', '1', 'Cut each rutabaga slice into quarters.'),
('20670', '2', 'Combine rutabaga, turnips, parsnip, and carrot in an 8-quart stockpot; cover with water. Bring to a boil, and cook 30 minutes or until tender.'),
('20670', '3', 'Drain. Stir in sugar and next 4 ingredients (sugar through pepper). Spoon vegetable mixture into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray.'),
('20670', '4', 'Spread Cheese Sauce over vegetable mixture.'),
('20670', '5', 'Preheat oven to 35'),
('20670', '6', 'Place bread in a food processor; pulse 10 times or until crumbly to measure 1 cup. Sprinkle crumbs on a baking sheet; bake at 350 for 5 minutes or until golden.'),
('20670', '7', 'Combine breadcrumbs and butter in a small bowl; sprinkle over sauce.'),
('20670', '8', 'Bake at 350 for 25 minutes or until bubbly.'),
('20670', '9', 'Let stand 10 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley.'),
('20671', '1', 'Heat oil and butter in a 12-inch heavy skillet over moderate heat until hot but not smoking, then cook turnips, stirring occasionally, until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.'),
('20671', '2', 'Add parsnips and shallots and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown and almost tender, about 10 minutes.'),
('20671', '3', 'Add garlic, rosemary, and salt and pepper to taste and cook, stirring, until vegetables are tender, about 3 minutes more.'),
('20672', '1', 'Season the chops with salt and pepper, to taste. Beat the egg with salt and pepper and dip each chop in the egg and then in the bread crumbs.'),
('20672', '2', 'In a large skillet, heat the oil over high heat and add the chops, working in batches if necessary, and cook until deep golden brown on both sides, about 10 minutes.'),
('20672', '3', 'Meanwhile, in a small saucepan, heat the butter over medium-low heat until it melts, then whisk in the flour, stirring constantly until it is dissolved.'),
('20672', '4', 'Whisk in the stock, a little at a time, then stir in the horseradish and cook for 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste, and pour over the chops.'),
('20672', '5', 'In a large, heavy-bottomed saucepan, heat the oil over high heat until smoking.'),
('20672', '6', 'Add all the chicken parts and brown all over, stirring to avoid burning.'),
('20672', '7', 'Remove the chicken and reserve.'),
('20672', '8', 'Add the carrots, onions, and celery to the pot and cook until soft and browned. Return the chicken to the pot and add 3 quarts of water, the tomato paste, peppercorns, and parsley. Stir with a wooden spoon to dislodge the browned chicken and vegetables bits from the bottom of the pan. Bring almost to a boil, then reduce heat and cook at a low simmer until reduced by half, about 2 hours, occasionally skimming excess fat.'),
('20672', '9', 'Remove from heat, strain, and press on the solids with the bottom of a ladle to extract out all liquids. Stir the stock to facilitate cooling and set aside. Refrigerate stock in small containers for up to a week or freeze for up to a month.'),
('20672', '10', 'Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F.'),
('20672', '11', 'Place the turnips in a large pot and cover with water.'),
('20672', '12', 'Add 2 tablespoons salt, bring to a boil, and cook until tender.'),
('20672', '13', 'Cut the turnips into 5 pieces each and place in a casserole. Cover with the besciamella and Parmigiano. Season with salt and pepper, and bake for 30 minutes, until the besciamella is bubbling and the top is browned.'),
('20672', '14', 'In a medium saucepan, heat butter until melted.'),
('20672', '15', 'Add flour and stir until smooth. Over medium heat, cook until light golden brown, about 6 to 7 minutes.'),
('20672', '16', 'Meanwhile, heat milk in separate pan until just about to boil.'),
('20672', '17', 'Add milk to butter mixture 1 cup at a time, whisking continuously until very smooth and bring to a boil. Cook 10 minutes and remove from heat. Season with salt and nutmeg and set aside.'),
('20678', '1', 'Preheat oven to 30'),
('20678', '2', 'Place flour in a shallow dish.'),
('20678', '3', 'Heat oil in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat. Sprinkle beef evenly on all sides with 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper; dredge in flour.'),
('20678', '4', 'Add beef to pan; cook 10 minutes, turning to brown on all sides.'),
('20678', '5', 'Add broth and next 3 ingredients (through bay leaf), scraping pan to remove browned bits; bring to a boil. Cover and bake at 300 for 1 1/2 hours.'),
('20678', '6', 'Add carrots; cover and cook 25 minutes.'),
('20678', '7', 'Add remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt, turnips, and onion; cover and cook an additional 1 hour and 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender and beef is fork-tender.'),
('20678', '8', 'Remove beef and vegetables from pan; discard bay leaf. Cover beef mixture; keep warm.'),
('20678', '9', 'Let cooking liquid stand 10 minutes.'),
('20678', '10', 'Place a zip-top plastic bag inside a 2-cup glass measure.'),
('20678', '11', 'Pour cooking liquid into bag; let stand 10 minutes (fat will rise to the top). Seal bag; carefully snip off 1 bottom corner of bag.'),
('20678', '12', 'Drain cooking liquid into a medium bowl, stopping before fat layer reaches opening; discard fat.'),
('20678', '13', 'Serve cooking liquid with beef and vegetables. Sprinkle each serving with 1 tablespoon parsley.'),
('20683', '1', 'Cut beef into 2- to 2 1/2-inch pieces; pat with paper towels to absorb excess moisture.'),
('20683', '2', 'Combine 3 Tbsp. flour, 1 tsp. salt, paprika, and pepper in a bowl; toss beef with flour mixture.'),
('20683', '3', 'Cook beef, in batches, in hot oil in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat, stirring often, 4 to 6 minutes or until brown.'),
('20683', '4', 'Remove beef from Dutch oven.'),
('20683', '5', 'Add red wine, stirring to loosen particles from bottom of Dutch oven. Return beef to Dutch oven; add broth, thyme, bay leaf, and 1/2 tsp. salt. Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat to low, and cook, stirring occasionally, 1 hour.'),
('20683', '6', 'Meanwhile, peel turnip, and cut into 1-inch cubes. Halve mushrooms.'),
('20683', '7', 'Add turnip, mushrooms, and carrots to stew. Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until meat is fork-tender.'),
('20683', '8', 'Whisk together remaining 1 Tbsp. flour and 1/4 tsp. salt until blended; whisk 1/2 cup hot broth into flour mixture until smooth.'),
('20683', '9', 'Whisk flour mixture into stew until smooth. Cook, stirring often, 20 minutes or until thickened.'),
('20683', '10', '*Beef broth may be substituted.'),
('20687', '1', 'Preheat oven to 500°F.'),
('20687', '2', 'Cut the turnips in half, and then each half into three wedges.'),
('20687', '3', 'In a small roasting pan, pour in the olive oil.  Toss in the wedges, and cut them on all sides in the oil.'),
('20687', '4', 'Place in the oven for 15 minutes.'),
('20687', '5', 'Remove, flip the turnips onto an uncooked side.'),
('20687', '6', 'Place back in the oven for 7 minutes.'),
('20687', '7', 'Remove from the oven and turn on the last uncooked side.'),
('20687', '8', 'Meanwhile, whisk together the honey, hot water, cinnamon, nutmeg, and kosher salt in a small bowl.'),
('20687', '9', 'Pour over the turnips.'),
('20687', '10', 'Place back in the oven for a final five minutes.'),
('20687', '11', 'Remove and serve.'),
('20688', '1', 'Stir fennel seeds in small dry skillet over medium heat until very fragrant and slightly darker in color, about 3 minutes.'),
('20688', '2', 'Add coarse salt; stir to blend.'),
('20688', '3', 'Remove from heat; cool.'),
('20688', '4', 'Transfer fennel seed mixture to spice mill; grind until fennel seeds are just coarsely chopped (do not grind to powder). DO AHEAD: Can be made 2 days ahead. Store airtight at room temperature.'),
('20688', '5', 'Arrange fennel slices and turnip wedges on platter; garnish with fennel fronds.'),
('20688', '6', 'Serve vegetables with fennel salt.'),
('20690', '1', 'Preheat oven to 450°F with rack in middle.'),
('20690', '2', 'Melt butter in an ovenproof 12-inch heavy skillet, then cool.'),
('20690', '3', 'Slice turnips paper-thin with slicer, then arrange one third of slices, overlapping tightly, in skillet, keeping remaining slices covered with dampened paper towels. Sprinkle with about a third of thyme, savory, kosher salt, and cayenne. Make 2 more layers.'),
('20690', '4', 'Cook, covered, over medium heat until underside is browned, about 10 minutes.'),
('20690', '5', 'Add cream and cook, covered, until center is tender, 20 to 25 minutes.'),
('20690', '6', 'Sprinkle evenly with cheese, then bake, uncovered, until golden and bubbling, 10 to 15 minutes.'),
('20690', '7', 'Let stand 5 minutes before serving.'),
('20693', '1', 'In a large pot, bring the chicken stock to a simmer.'),
('20693', '2', 'Add the chicken breasts and simmer over moderate heat until just cooked through, about 20 minutes.'),
('20693', '3', 'Transfer the chicken to a plate to cool slightly, then pull into shreds.'),
('20693', '4', 'Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, mix the flours with the Parmesan, milk and egg. Season with 1/4 teaspoon of salt and 1/4 teaspoon of pepper.'),
('20693', '5', 'Transfer to a pastry bag fitted with a 1/4-inch round tip.'),
('20693', '6', 'Add the carrot, parsnip, squash and turnip to the stock and season with salt and pepper. Cover partially and cook over moderate heat until the vegetables are just tender, about 10 minutes.'),
('20693', '7', 'Add the leek and cook until tender. Holding the pastry bag in 1 hand and a table knife in the other, cut 1-inch lengths of the dumpling dough into the simmering soup. When all of the dough has been added, stir gently and cook until tender, about 2 minutes.'),
('20693', '8', 'Add the shredded chicken, cook until heated through and serve.'),
('20697', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 40'),
('20697', '2', 'Divide the rutabagas, turnips and carrots between 2 large rimmed baking sheets.'),
('20697', '3', 'Drizzle 1 tablespoon of the oil over each sheet of vegetables and toss well.'),
('20697', '4', 'Spread the vegetables out in an even layer and season with salt and pepper. Roast until lightly browned and tender, about 40 minutes.'),
('20697', '5', 'Drizzle 1 tablespoon of the vinegar over each pan of vegetables and toss well. Roast until sizzling, about 3 minutes longer.'),
('20697', '6', 'Meanwhile, in a small skillet, bring the chicken broth and maple syrup to a boil over high heat. Boil until reduced to 1/4 cup, about 20 minutes.'),
('20697', '7', 'Remove from the heat and whisk in the butter.'),
('20697', '8', 'Transfer the root vegetables to a warmed bowl.'),
('20697', '9', 'Add the maple glaze and toss well.'),
('20697', '10', 'Serve right away.'),
('20702', '1', 'Preheat oven to 42'),
('20702', '2', 'Place 8 thyme sprigs, beets, carrots, and turnips in a large bowl.'),
('20702', '3', 'Drizzle with 1 tablespoon oil; sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Toss to coat. Arrange vegetables in a jelly-roll pan.'),
('20702', '4', 'Bake at 425 for 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender and begin to brown, stirring occasionally.'),
('20702', '5', 'Place remaining 8 thyme sprigs, garlic, onions, and fennel in a bowl.'),
('20702', '6', 'Drizzle with remaining 1 tablespoon oil; sprinkle with remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Arrange vegetables in a single layer in a jelly-roll pan.'),
('20702', '7', 'Bake at 425 for 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender and begin to brown, stirring occasionally.'),
('20702', '8', 'Combine beet mixture and onion mixture; sprinkle with chopped thyme.'),
('20707', '1', 'Melt butter in a medium pot over medium-high heat.'),
('20707', '2', 'Add onion and 1/2 tsp. salt. Cook, stirring, until soft, about 2 minutes.'),
('20707', '3', 'Add turnips, parsnips, broth, and 1 cup water. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium-low and simmer until vegetables are tender, 10 to 15 minutes.'),
('20707', '4', 'Meanwhile, combine pork, 1 tbsp. chives, parsley, cheese, 1/2 tsp. salt, and 1/4 tsp. pepper in a small bowl.'),
('20707', '5', 'Mix gently to combine. Form into 36 balls, about 1 tsp. each, and set aside.'),
('20707', '6', 'Whirl soup in a blender until smooth (in batches if necessary). Return to pot and keep warm over low heat.'),
('20707', '7', 'In a wide, shallow pan, bring at least 2 in. of water to a boil and add remaining 1 tsp. salt.'),
('20707', '8', 'Add meatballs and cook until they float to the surface and are cooked through (test one to be sure), about 4 minutes.'),
('20707', '9', 'Transfer to a warm plate with a slotted spoon.'),
('20707', '10', 'Divide soup among 6 bowls. Top each bowl with 6 meatballs and sprinkle with additional chives and pepper.'),
('20707', '11', 'Serve hot.'),
('20710', '1', 'Combine the carrots, turnips, onion, garlic, tomatoes (with their liquid), broth, salt, cumin, and pepper flakes in a 4- to 6-quart slow cooker. Cook on low heat for 6 hours, or on high for 3 hours.'),
('20710', '2', 'Add the zucchini and chickpeas and cook 1 hour longer on low.'),
('20711', '1', 'Arrange the sliced vegetables in separate piles on 2 large rimmed baking sheets. In a small bowl, whisk the vinegar with the olive oil and season with salt and pepper.'),
('20711', '2', 'Drizzle the dressing over the vegetables and toss each pile separately.'),
('20711', '3', 'Let stand for at least 15 minutes or up to 1 hour.'),
('20711', '4', 'Meanwhile, bring a medium saucepan of water to a boil. Carefully lower the eggs into the saucepan and reduce the heat to moderate. Simmer the eggs for 6 minutes.'),
('20711', '5', 'Pour off the hot water and gently shake the eggs in the pan to crack the shells. Fill the pan with cold water and let stand for 1 minute. Carefully peel the eggs. Reheat the peeled eggs for 2 minutes in 2 inches of simmering water.'),
('20711', '6', 'Drain and pat dry then halve the eggs.'),
('20711', '7', 'Arrange the vegetables on plates and top with the toasts and the soft-boiled eggs. Sprinkle the eggs and salads with fleur de sel and serve.'),
('20713', '1', 'In a large saucepan, bring the chicken stock to a simmer.'),
('20713', '2', 'Add the carrots and cook over moderate heat until tender, about 10 minutes. Using a slotted spoon, transfer the carrots to a plate.'),
('20713', '3', 'Add the turnips to the stock and cook until tender, about 6 minutes.'),
('20713', '4', 'Add to the plate of carrots. Simmer the scallions for 5 minutes and add them to the plate. Simmer the mushrooms just until tender, about 4 minutes; add to the plate.'),
('20713', '5', 'Add the chicken breasts to the simmering stock and poach at a bare simmer until just cooked through, about 12 minutes.'),
('20713', '6', 'Transfer the chicken to a plate and let rest for 5 minutes. Return the vegetables to the stock to reheat them; season with salt and pepper.'),
('20713', '7', 'Remove the skin from the chicken and slice each breast diagonally 1/3 inch thick. Divide the vegetables among 8 shallow bowls. Arrange the chicken over the vegetables and add the hot broth.'),
('20714', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 35'),
('20714', '2', 'Put the shallots on a large piece of foil and top with 1/2 tablespoon of the butter. Season with salt and pepper and seal the shallots in the foil.'),
('20714', '3', 'Bake for about 30 minutes, or until tender.'),
('20714', '4', 'In a large saucepan, combine the parsnips, turnips, carrots, leeks, chicken stock, thyme and the remaining 2 tablespoons of butter. Bring to a boil over moderately high heat, then reduce the heat to low and add a pinch each of salt and pepper. Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until the vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes. Discard the thyme sprig.'),
('20714', '5', 'In a medium saucepan, cook the potatoes in boiling salted water until tender, about 10 minutes.'),
('20714', '6', 'Drain the potatoes and cut them into 2-inch cubes.'),
('20714', '7', 'Add the potatoes and roasted shallots to the vegetable stew, season with salt and pepper and serve.'),
('20715', '1', 'In a medium pot of simmering salted water, cook the asparagus over moderately high heat until tender, about 4 minutes. Using a slotted spoon, transfer the asparagus to a bowl.'),
('20715', '2', 'Add the cranberry beans to the water and simmer over moderate heat until tender, about 40 minutes.'),
('20715', '3', 'Drain the beans and transfer to the bowl.'),
('20715', '4', 'Meanwhile, in a medium enameled, cast-iron casserole, heat 1/2 tablespoon of the olive oil.'),
('20715', '5', 'Add the scallions and cook over moderate heat until barely tender, about 1 minute.'),
('20715', '6', 'Transfer the scallions to the bowl with the asparagus.'),
('20715', '7', 'Add another 1/2 tablespoon of the olive oil to the casserole.'),
('20715', '8', 'Add the mushrooms, season with salt, cover and cook over moderate heat, stirring a few times, until lightly browned and tender, about 3 minutes.'),
('20715', '9', 'Transfer the mushrooms to the bowl.'),
('20715', '10', 'Heat the remaining 1 tablespoon of olive oil in the casserole.'),
('20715', '11', 'Add the turnips and carrots, season with salt and cook over moderate heat for 1 minute.'),
('20715', '12', 'Add 1 cup of the stock, cover and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes.'),
('20715', '13', 'Add another 1/2 cup of the stock, cover and cook until the turnips and carrots are tender, about 10 minutes longer.'),
('20715', '14', 'Add the zucchini and 1/2 cup of the stock and simmer until the zucchini is just tender, about 4 minutes.'),
('20715', '15', 'Add the remaining 1/4 cup of stock to the casserole along with the lemon zest, lemon juice and lettuce and cook, stirring, until the lettuce just wilts, about 20 seconds. Stir in the crme frache.'),
('20715', '16', 'Add the asparagus, beans, scallions and mushrooms to the stew. Simmer briefly, until heated through, about 30 seconds.'),
('20715', '17', 'Add the chervil and chives and serve the stew in bowls.'),
('20718', '1', 'Remove bulbs from leeks, reserving green parts for another use.'),
('20718', '2', 'Cut bulbs into 1 1/2-inch pieces.'),
('20718', '3', 'Remove and discard fennel fronds and outside layer of fennel bulb.'),
('20718', '4', 'Cut fennel into slices.'),
('20718', '5', 'Toss together sliced leek bulbs, fennel, carrots, and next 4 ingredients.'),
('20718', '6', 'Place in a 13- x 9-inch roasting pan.'),
('20718', '7', 'Add beets; sprinkle vegetables with salt and pepper.'),
('20718', '8', 'Bake at 400 for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender, stirring twice.'),
('20723', '1', 'Preheat oven to 35'),
('20723', '2', 'Melt butter in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('20723', '3', 'Add mushrooms to pan, and saut 2 minutes or until lightly browned. Stir in garlic; saut 30 seconds.'),
('20723', '4', 'Add wine; cook 2 minutes.'),
('20723', '5', 'Add parsley, thyme, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 10 minutes. Uncover and cook 6 minutes or until liquid almost evaporates.'),
('20723', '6', 'Remove from heat; discard thyme.'),
('20723', '7', 'Add cream cheese, stirring until cheese melts.'),
('20723', '8', 'Remove mushroom mixture from pan. Wipe pan clean with paper towels.'),
('20723', '9', 'Heat pan over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray.'),
('20723', '10', 'Add onion; saute for 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Reduce heat to medium; continue cooking for 15 minutes or until deep golden brown, stirring frequently. Set aside.'),
('20723', '11', 'Coat a 6-cup baking dish with cooking spray. Arrange potato slices in dish, and top with spinach. Sprinkle 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon black pepper evenly over spinach. Spoon the mushroom mixture over black pepper, and arrange turnip slices over mushroom mixture. Top with caramelized onions; sprinkle with remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt, remaining 1/4 teaspoon black pepper, and tarragon.'),
('20723', '12', 'Pour whipping cream over tarragon, and sprinkle evenly with Gruyre cheese. Cover and bake at 350 for 40 minutes. Uncover and bake an additional 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender and cheese begins to brown.'),
('20725', '1', 'Brown beef in oil in a large stew pot.'),
('20725', '2', 'Add all vegetables, except tomatoes, and saute over medium-low heat for 5 minutes.'),
('20725', '3', 'Sprinkle flour over meat and vegetables and stir to coat.'),
('20725', '4', 'Add broth, wine or broth, seasonings and tomatoes. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours, or until meat is very tender, stirring occasionally.'),
('20726', '1', 'Cut off pointed end of garlic just to expose cloves.'),
('20726', '2', 'Combine garlic and the remaining ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Reduce heat, and simmer 50 minutes. Strain through a fine sieve over a bowl; discard solids. Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator up to 1 week.'),
('20727', '1', 'Peel potatoes and turnips, then cut into 2-inch pieces. Cover potatoes, turnips, and 2 teaspoons salt by 2 inches cold water in a 6-quart pot. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until potatoes are tender, 15 to 18 minutes.'),
('20727', '2', 'While vegetables cook, melt 3 tablespoons butter in a 10-inch heavy skillet (preferably cast-iron), then toast bread crumbs with remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt, stirring frequently, until golden brown, 3 to 5 minutes.'),
('20727', '3', 'Add horseradish and toss until combined well, then transfer to a small bowl.'),
